# Uncertainty Map — {{ project.name }}

The uncertainty map is the explicit catalog of what {{ project.name }} does **not** know.
Every project has unknown unknowns; this map converts them to **known unknowns** — which
are far less dangerous.

An entry here means: "We know we don't know this. Here is what we're doing about it."

Evidence gaps and unresolved uncertainty are surfaced by `specsmith audit` and
summarized by `specsmith inspect`.

